1. Collect or Simulate Data:
    Create two columns (e.g., X = Hours Studied, Y = Marks Scored).
    Enter at least 10 pairs of values.
2. Create Scatter Plot in Excel:
    Select both columns.
    Insert → Charts → Scatter Plot.
    Add chart title and axis labels.
3. Calculate Covariance:
    Use the formula:
    =COVARIANCE.P(array1, array2)
